   "source": [
    "# Exercise 7: Reinforcement Learning I\n",
    "\n",
    "#### Lukas Dippold, Evert de Man"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-13T14:00:58.492060Z",

   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from scipy.special import logsumexp\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### (1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-13T14:00:58.522864Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-13T14:00:58.504017Z"
    },
    "collapsed": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#10 uniform numbers \n",
    "L = np.random.uniform(0., 0.9, 10)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### (2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-13T14:01:07.123929Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-13T14:01:07.116840Z"
    },
    "collapsed": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#time and lives=instantiations of the agent (you need multiple instantiations for a general statement)\n",
    "\n",
    "def generate_reward(lever):\n",
    "    return np.random.choice([0,1], p=[1-L[lever], L[lever]])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-13T14:01:12.220552Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-13T14:01:08.123183Z"
    },
    "collapsed": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "it = 10000\n",
    "bandit = np.zeros([10,it])\n",
    "\n",
    "for a in range(10):\n",
    "    for i in range (it):\n",
    "        bandit[a,i] = generate_reward(a)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-13T14:01:12.248069Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-13T14:01:12.223488Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Difference to reward probabilities:\n",
      "\n",
      " [-0.00481918 -0.00178567 -0.00385875 -0.00298117  0.00440666 -0.00731385\n",
      " -0.00170781  0.00113576  0.0062396   0.005465  ]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print('Difference to reward probabilities:\\n\\n',np.mean(bandit,axis=1)-L)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### (3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-13T14:01:12.444996Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-13T14:01:12.432742Z"
    },
    "collapsed": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class Q():\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __init__(self, size, eta=0.01):\n",
    "        self.values = np.zeros(size)\n",
    "        self.learnrate = eta\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def update(self, i):\n",
    "        r = generate_reward(i)\n",
    "        self.values[i] = self.values[i] + self.learnrate*(r-self.values[i])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### (4)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-13T14:01:13.052637Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-13T14:01:13.039057Z"
    },
    "collapsed": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def eps_greedy(qv, eps):\n",
    "    max_q = np.max(qv.values)\n",
    "    if (np.random.uniform(0,1) <= (1-eps)):\n",
    "        max_i, = np.where(qv.values == max_q)\n",
    "        return max_i.tolist(), max_q\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        rind = np.random.randint(0,9)\n",
    "        return [rind], max_q\n",
    "    \n",
    "#return lever index always as a list as it is possible that this are more than one"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### (5)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-13T14:59:18.867043Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-13T14:59:17.240230Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x10e5ffef0>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "#plot expected reward -> he will change it! plot the estimated expected reward = Q-value\n",
    "eps = 0\n",
    "it = 1000\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "\n",
    "for j in range(20):\n",
    "    q = Q(10)\n",
    "    max_q_list = []\n",
    "    for i in range(it):\n",
    "        lever_index, max_q = eps_greedy(q, eps)\n",
    "        max_q_list.append(max_q)\n",
    "        for ind in lever_index:\n",
    "            q.update(ind)\n",
    "    ax.plot(max_q_list)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- The agent does not consistently identify the levers with the largest reward posibilties. In that case, they would all end up with the same maximum Q-value which they do not.\n",
    "- With the greedy policy, the agent can get stuck in a lever with the highest Q-value but not the truely highest reward. It is not exploring much but starts to exploit too quickly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### (6)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-12T12:47:48.372449Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-12T12:47:18.236095Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x11dc3b630>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "eps = [0.0,0.01,0.1,0.5]\n",
    "it = 1000\n",
    "lives = 100\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "\n",
    "for e in eps:\n",
    "    maxQ = np.zeros([lives,it])\n",
    "    for j in range(lives):\n",
    "        q = Q(10)\n",
    "        for i in range(it):\n",
    "            lever_index, max_q = eps_greedy(q,e)\n",
    "            maxQ[j,i] = max_q\n",
    "            for ind in lever_index:\n",
    "                q.update(ind)\n",
    "    ax.plot(np.mean(maxQ,axis=0), label= r\"$\\epsilon =$ \" +str(e))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.axhline(np.max(L),color='red')\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"trial number\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Q-value\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- For all epsilons, the maximum expected reward is not reached. For $\\epsilon = 0.0$ it is not reached because it gets  stuck with bad Q-values as analysed in task (5). \n",
    "- When $\\epsilon$ gets higher than 0, there is an uncertainty pushing the Q-value away from the maximum value, so with growing $\\epsilon$ the expected reward does not result in the optimal value either."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### (7)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-12T12:16:14.245428Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-12T12:16:14.235836Z"
    },
    "collapsed": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#softmax is not numerically stable if input arguments get too large -> use logsumexp\n",
    "def softmax(qv,beta):\n",
    "    P = np.exp(beta * qv.values - logsumexp(beta * qv.values))\n",
    "    maxQ = np.max(qv.values)\n",
    "    lever = np.random.choice(range(10), p=P)\n",
    "    return lever, maxQ"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-12T12:22:42.646197Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-12T12:16:14.249411Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x11da07ef0>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "betas = [1, 5, 15, 50]\n",
    "it = 5000\n",
    "lives = 100\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots()\n",
    "\n",
    "for b in betas:\n",
    "    maxQ = np.zeros([lives,it])\n",
    "    for j in range(lives):\n",
    "        q = Q(10)\n",
    "        for i in range(it):\n",
    "            lever_index, max_q = softmax(q,b)\n",
    "            maxQ[j,i] = max_q\n",
    "            q.update(lever_index)\n",
    "    ax.plot(np.mean(maxQ,axis=0), label=str(b))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.axhline(np.max(L),color='red')\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"trial number\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Q-value\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "- There is a strong improvement compared to the $\\epsilon$-greedy policy. for the low beta values we even cross maximum expected reward. the higher beta, the quicker the policy explores but also starts exploiting quicker in suboptimal levers. a beta value of one explores slowly everything and needs some time to reach the maximum. a beta of 5 seems to handle the exploitation/ exploration dilemma best "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### (8)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {

   "source": [
    "#modified reward function for reward -5000\n",
    "def generate_reward_mod(lever):\n",
    "    if lever == 9:\n",
    "        return -5000\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        return np.random.choice([0,1], p=[1-L[lever],L[lever]])\n",
    "\n",
    "class Q_mod():\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def __init__(self,size,eta=0.01):\n",
    "        self.values = np.zeros(size)\n",
    "        self.learnrate = eta\n",
    "    \n",
    "    def update(self,i):\n",
    "        r = generate_reward_mod(i)\n",
    "        self.values[i] = self.values[i] + self.learnrate*(r-self.values[i])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   },
   "outputs": [

     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "beta = 15\n",
    "eps = 0.1\n",
    "it = 5000\n",
    "lives = 500\n",
    "\n",
    "maxQG = np.zeros([lives,it])\n",
    "maxQS = np.zeros([lives,it])\n",
    "\n",
    "for j in range(lives):\n",
    "    qG = Q_mod(10)   #greedy\n",
    "    qS = Q_mod(10)   #softmax\n",
    "    for i in range(it):\n",
    "        #greedy\n",
    "        lever_indexG, max_qG = eps_greedy(qG,eps)\n",
    "        maxQG[j,i] = max_qG\n",
    "        for ind in lever_indexG:\n",
    "                qG.update(ind)\n",
    "        #softmax\n",
    "        lever_indexS, max_qS = softmax(qS,beta)\n",
    "        maxQS[j,i] = max_qS\n",
    "        qS.update(lever_indexS)\n",
    "        \n",
    "plt.plot(np.mean(maxQG,axis=0), label='Greedy policy')\n",
    "plt.plot(np.mean(maxQS,axis=0), label='Softmax policy')\n",
    "    \n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.axhline(np.max(L),color='red')\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"iterations\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {

   "source": [
    "#### (9)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 33,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-12T15:24:05.416492Z",

   "source": [
    "b = [0.1, 0.4, 1.6, 6.4, 25.6]\n",
    "\n",
    "def B(i, b):\n",
    "    beta = 1 + i/b\n",
    "    return beta\n",
    "\n",
    "lives = 100\n",
    "its = 2000"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 36,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2018-06-12T15:33:21.980153Z",
     "start_time": "2018-06-12T15:29:33.967141Z"
    },
    "collapsed": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "beta = 5\n",
    "\n",
    "maxQS_cb = np.zeros([lives, its]) #constant beta\n",
    "maxQS_vb = np.zeros([lives, its, len(b)]) \n",
    "\n",
    "for j in range(lives):\n",
    "    qS = Q(10)   #softmax\n",
    "    for i in range(its):\n",
    "        #softmax\n",
    "        lever_indexS, max_qS = softmax(qS, beta)\n",
    "        maxQS_cb[j,i] = max_qS\n",
    "        qS.update(lever_indexS)\n",
    "        # Softmax with variable beta\n",
    "        for k, b_ in enumerate(b):\n",
    "            vb = B(i, b_)\n",
    "            lever_indexS, max_qS = softmax(qS, vb)\n",
    "            maxQS_vb[j, i, k] = max_qS\n",
    "            qS.update(lever_indexS)"
   ]
